{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "Markov chain",
  "settings": { "numSamples": 10000 },
  "sheets": [
    {
      "name": "Unrolled",
      "cells": {
        "A1": "Employment Markov chain (unrolled, one row per step)",
        "A3": "Month",
        "B3": "Employed? (1=yes)",
        "C3": "Monthly income ($)",
        "A4": "0",
        "B4": "state0 = 1",
        "C4": ":= if(state0, Normal(5000, 500), Normal(1500, 300))",
        "A5": "1",
        "B5": ":= if(B4, Bernoulli(0.95), Bernoulli(0.20))",
        "C5": ":= if(B5, Normal(5000, 500), Normal(1500, 300))",
        "A6": "2",
        "B6": ":= if(B5, Bernoulli(0.95), Bernoulli(0.20))",
        "C6": ":= if(B6, Normal(5000, 500), Normal(1500, 300))",
        "A7": "3",
        "B7": ":= if(B6, Bernoulli(0.95), Bernoulli(0.20))",
        "C7": ":= if(B7, Normal(5000, 500), Normal(1500, 300))",
        "A8": "4",
        "B8": ":= if(B7, Bernoulli(0.95), Bernoulli(0.20))",
        "C8": ":= if(B8, Normal(5000, 500), Normal(1500, 300))",
        "A9": "5",
        "B9": ":= if(B8, Bernoulli(0.95), Bernoulli(0.20))",
        "C9": ":= if(B9, Normal(5000, 500), Normal(1500, 300))",
        "A10": "6",
        "B10": ":= if(B9, Bernoulli(0.95), Bernoulli(0.20))",
        "C10": ":= if(B10, Normal(5000, 500), Normal(1500, 300))",
        "A11": "7",
        "B11": ":= if(B10, Bernoulli(0.95), Bernoulli(0.20))",
        "C11": ":= if(B11, Normal(5000, 500), Normal(1500, 300))",
        "A12": "8",
        "B12": ":= if(B11, Bernoulli(0.95), Bernoulli(0.20))",
        "C12": ":= if(B12, Normal(5000, 500), Normal(1500, 300))",
        "A13": "9",
        "B13": ":= if(B12, Bernoulli(0.95), Bernoulli(0.20))",
        "C13": ":= if(B13, Normal(5000, 500), Normal(1500, 300))",
        "A14": "10",
        "B14": ":= if(B13, Bernoulli(0.95), Bernoulli(0.20))",
        "C14": ":= if(B14, Normal(5000, 500), Normal(1500, 300))",
        "A15": "11",
        "B15": ":= if(B14, Bernoulli(0.95), Bernoulli(0.20))",
        "C15": ":= if(B15, Normal(5000, 500), Normal(1500, 300))",
        "A16": "12",
        "B16": ":= if(B15, Bernoulli(0.95), Bernoulli(0.20))",
        "C16": ":= if(B16, Normal(5000, 500), Normal(1500, 300))",
        "A18": "Total income (12 months)",
        "C18": ":= sum(C4:C16)",
        "A19": "Employment rate at month 12",
        "B19": ":= B16",
        "A20": "Average monthly income",
        "C20": ":= mean(C4:C16)"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Chain",
      "cells": {
        "A1": "Same model using Chain (one cell per process)",
        "A3": "Transition parameters",
        "A4": "P(keep job)",
        "B4": "pKeep = 0.95",
        "A5": "P(find job)",
        "B5": "pFind = 0.20",
        "A7": "Employment chain",
        "B7": "employed = Chain(if(employed, Bernoulli(pKeep), Bernoulli(pFind)), 1)",
        "A8": "State at month 12",
        "B8": ":= employed[12]",
        "A10": "Income chain (synced with employment)",
        "B10": "income = Chain(if(employed, Normal(5000, 500), Normal(1500, 300)), Normal(5000, 500))",
        "A11": "Income at month 12",
        "B11": ":= income[12]",
        "A12": "Total income (12 months)",
        "B12": ":= sum(income[1:12])",
        "A13": "Average monthly income",
        "B13": ":= mean(income[1:12])",
        "A15": "Notes",
        "A16": "The Chain version does the same thing as the Unrolled sheet,",
        "A17": "but in a single cell per process. Click the Chain cells to",
        "A18": "see the Timeline fan chart showing all 12 steps.",
        "A19": "The income chain references the employed chain, so they",
        "A20": "stay synchronized (step 5 of income uses step 5 of employed).",
        "A22": "sum(income[1:12]) adds steps 1 through 12 of the",
        "A23": "income chain — the distribution of total annual income.",
        "A24": "Each step gets fresh samples automatically."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Markov",
      "cells": {
        "A1": "Same model using Markov() — transition diagram syntax",
        "A3": "1. Define emission distributions (one per state)",
        "A4": "Employed income",
        "B4": "emp = Normal(5000, 500)",
        "A5": "Unemployed income",
        "B5": "unemp = Normal(1500, 300)",
        "A7": "2. Define the Markov chain",
        "A8": "Income process",
        "B8": "income = Markov(emp: 0.95 -> emp, 0.05 -> unemp; unemp: 0.2 -> emp)",
        "A10": "3. Aggregate over steps",
        "A11": "Total income (12 months)",
        "B11": ":= sum(income[1:12])",
        "A12": "Average monthly income",
        "B12": ":= mean(income[1:12])",
        "A13": "P5 of total income",
        "B13": ":= P(sum(income[1:12]), 5)",
        "A15": "How it works",
        "A16": "State names (emp, unemp) are variables holding",
        "A17": "emission distributions. Each step, the chain",
        "A18": "transitions between states and samples from the",
        "A19": "current state's distribution.",
        "A21": "The first state listed is the initial state.",
        "A22": "Use 'init' to override: init unemp",
        "A23": "Probabilistic init also works: init: 0.5 -> emp, 0.5 -> unemp",
        "A25": "Missing probability mass goes to self-transition.",
        "A26": "Above, unemp only specifies 0.2 -> emp, so the",
        "A27": "remaining 0.8 stays in unemp automatically.",
        "A29": "States can also define emissions inline:",
        "B29": "inc = Markov(e = Normal(5000, 500): 0.95 -> e, 0.05 -> u; u = Normal(1500, 300): 0.2 -> e)",
        "A30": "This is fully self-contained — no separate cells needed.",
        "A32": "Click a Markov cell to see the Timeline fan chart.",
        "A33": "income[5] accesses the distribution at step 5 of the chain."
      }
    }
  ]
}
